op.Full Obit Text: Glenn Milton Goodin passed away on March 22, 2023, in Traverse City Michigan. Born January 7, 1937, in Douglas, Michigan, he was the son of the late Raymond and Cretora (Leach) Goodin. Glenn attended Saugatuck High School, was a builder by trade, beginning his career building homes, moving to commercial building in partnership as Goodin & Bigelow Construction and later with his company, GM Construction. Many commercial buildings can be seen in the Traverse City area, evidence of Glenn's skill in building., He was preceded in death by his first wife, Myrtle; his stepson, Calvin Overbeek; and his sister, Beth Goodin Carfagno., He is survived by his wife, Donna; two daughters, Robin (David) Henning and Margo (James) Van Oeffelen;  stepson, Ross (Joan) Overbeek; sister, Iva (David) Meadows-Klopfenstein; four grandchildren; and three great-grandchildren., Glenn will be laid to rest in Fennville Cemetery.  Chappell Funeral Home is assisting the family with arrangements., There will be a memorial service at Vriesland Church of God 7th Day, Wednesday, March 29th at 3:30pm with a light meal to follow. Located at 6456 Byron Road in Zeeland, MI 49464.,
